<h1 id="gma-title" style="color:#0d47a1;font-size:1.5em;font-weight:700;border-bottom:2px solid #90caf9;padding-bottom:0.25em;margin-top:0">Generic Markdown authoring (portable)</h1>

Copy into any repo’s **`.cursor/rules/`** for consistent, **scannable** long-form **`*.md`** and **`.mdc`** (YAML frontmatter + Markdown body).

**When to apply:** Whenever you **create, edit, or review** a **`*.md`** file or a **`.mdc`** rule whose body is Markdown.

**Trigger:** This rule has **`alwaysApply: true`** in this workspace so it **stays in agent context** by default—apply this spec to **all** new or edited **`*.md`** / **`.mdc`** files here. You can still include **`mrkd`** or **@**‑mention **`mrkd-markdown-authoring`** to stress the rule for a specific edit. (Cursor does not auto-enforce formatting in the editor; consistency depends on following this rule when authoring.)

**Portable copy:** You can copy **this single rule** into another repo’s **`.cursor/rules/`**; it already includes outline conventions plus **tables** and **Mermaid** (section 6).

<h2 id="gma-outline" style="color:#1565c0;font-size:1.22em;font-weight:650;border-left:4px solid #42a5f5;padding-left:10px;margin-top:1.1em">Document outline</h2>

1. [Non-negotiable: hierarchy, numbers, size, color](#gma-non-negotiable) — **read first** for `.md` / `.mdc` output.
2. [Structure principles](#gma-structure) — depth, section length.
3. [Document outline section](#gma-outline-section) — TOC pattern.
4. [Markdown heading syntax](#gma-md-headings) — `#` / `##` / `###` baseline.
5. [HTML headings for color and size](#gma-html-headings) — when and how.
6. [Visual aids: tables and Mermaid](#gma-visual-aids) — HTML tables, diagrams; patterns live in this rule.
    6.1 [HTML comparison tables](#gma-tables) — layout, badges, exemplar.
    6.2 [Mermaid diagrams](#gma-mermaid) — layout, colors, font, snippet.
7. [Colored inline text](#gma-inline-color) — badges, restraint.
8. [Fenced code blocks](#gma-fences) — language tags.
9. [Self-check before saving](#gma-self-check) — merge checklist.

