<h2 id="gma-structure" style="color:#1565c0;font-size:1.22em;font-weight:650;border-left:4px solid #42a5f5;padding-left:10px;margin-top:1.1em">2. Structure principles</h2>

- Organize content into a **clear outline** that follows the reader’s mental model (overview → detail → reference).
- Prefer **short sections** with descriptive titles over long undifferentiated blocks.

---

<h2 id="gma-outline-section" style="color:#1565c0;font-size:1.22em;font-weight:650;border-left:4px solid #42a5f5;padding-left:10px;margin-top:1.1em">3. Document outline section (for long docs)</h2>

The **first section after the document title** (and optional one-line type/status) should be **`## Table of Contents`** / **`## Document outline`** (pick one name per file and stay consistent).

- **List shape:** **Unordered** Markdown bullets (`-`) at the top level; **indent** subsections with **`  -`** and deeper items with **`    -`**. Every entry is a **`[Title](#anchor)`** hyperlink (optionally with section numbers **inside** the link text, e.g. `[3. Implementation](#implementation)`).
- **No redundant TOC numeration:** Do **not** use a leading **`1.`** / **`2.`** ordered-list marker **and** the same number inside the link—that renders as duplicated numbering in preview. Use **either** bullets with numbered link labels **or** (rarely) ordered lists with unnumbered link text—not both.
- **Hierarchy:** Nesting expresses structure; subsection labels such as **`5.1`** belong **in the link text**, not as a second Markdown list index.
- **Anchors must work:** **`#anchor`** must match the heading slug or explicit **`id`** on HTML headings (prefer explicit **`id`** when titles include emoji or punctuation).
- **Exception:** Trivial one-screen notes can skip the outline; **default** is a full TOC for anything longer or multi-topic.

<h3 id="gma-readme-emoji" style="color:#00695c;font-size:1.05em;font-weight:600;margin-top:0.85em">3.1 README files (`README.md`)</h3>

- For **repository or package `README.md`**, prefix each **major** section title (top-level body sections—typically **`##`** or styled **`h2`**) with **one professional emoji** that fits the topic (e.g. 🧠 concept, 🧩 architecture, 🔥 analytics, 🦾 integrations, 🏗 deployment).
- Use the **same emoji** in the **TOC link** and the **body heading**; keep subsections mostly emoji-free unless one icon aids scan (e.g. 📐 diagram).
- Prefer **clear, restrained** symbols—one emoji per major section, not decorative stacks.

**Example (pattern only — hierarchical hyperlinks, numbers inside links, no `1.` list markers):**

```markdown
## 📋 Table of Contents

- [🧠 1. Concept](#1-concept)
- [🧩 2. Architecture Overview](#2-architecture-overview)
  - [System layers](#system-layers)
  - [5.1 Data model](#data-model)
- [🔥 5. Analytics](#5-analytics)
  - [5.1 Ingest](#51-ingest)
```

