<h2 id="gma-md-headings" style="color:#1565c0;font-size:1.22em;font-weight:650;border-left:4px solid #42a5f5;padding-left:10px;margin-top:1.1em">4. Markdown heading syntax</h2>

- Use **`#` / `##` / `###`** so every renderer shows **distinct default sizes** even when HTML styling is stripped.
- Keep **one consistent scheme** per document (do not mix unrelated palettes with HTML).

---

<h2 id="gma-html-headings" style="color:#1565c0;font-size:1.22em;font-weight:650;border-left:4px solid #42a5f5;padding-left:10px;margin-top:1.1em">5. HTML headings for color and size</h2>

- Use HTML **`<h1>` / `<h2>` / `<h3>`** with **`id`** when you need **color and precise size** in Cursor preview or static sites that allow inline CSS.
- Prefer the **portable palette** in [Non-negotiable](#gma-non-negotiable).

