<h2 id="gma-inline-color" style="color:#1565c0;font-size:1.22em;font-weight:650;border-left:4px solid #42a5f5;padding-left:10px;margin-top:1.1em">7. Colored inline text</h2>

- **GitHub.com strips inline `style` (including `color`)** on `<span>`, `<a>`, and most headings in `README.md`. Cursor preview may show blue keyword tint; GitHub renders plain black text unless you use portable Markdown emphasis.
- **Portable keyword emphasis (GitHub + Cursor):**
  - **Concepts / product phrases:** `**bold**`
  - **Stack tokens** (clouds, tools, env names): `` `inline code` ``
  - **Cross-links:** `[label](#anchor)` or `[label](https://…)` (GitHub link blue)
- Use **`<span style="...">`** badges **only** for short labels in docs read **mostly in Cursor** (warnings, recommended)—same restraint as [table badges](#gma-table-text). For **repo root `README.md`**, prefer bold + backticks + links, not colored spans.
- Never rainbow-highlight long paragraphs.

---

<h2 id="gma-fences" style="color:#1565c0;font-size:1.22em;font-weight:650;border-left:4px solid #42a5f5;padding-left:10px;margin-top:1.1em">8. Fenced code blocks</h2>

- Always use a **language tag** on the opening fence: **`bash`**, **`python`**, **`yaml`**, **`json`**, **`text`**, **`mermaid`**, etc.
- Use **`text`** for logs and mixed snippets. Shell transcripts may use **`$`** / **`#`** prefixes when mimicking a session.

---

<h2 id="gma-self-check" style="color:#1565c0;font-size:1.22em;font-weight:650;border-left:4px solid #42a5f5;padding-left:10px;margin-top:1.1em">9. Self-check before saving</h2>

- [ ] **[Non-negotiable](#gma-non-negotiable)** satisfied: hierarchical TOC hyperlinks (no duplicate list + label numbering) + body numbering in headings (or justified exception) + three-level depth + **visible** title size/color.
- [ ] **Table of contents** is the **first** section (after title/metadata); **bullet** hierarchy; anchors match **`id`** or slug rules.
- [ ] **`README.md`:** major sections use **one matching emoji** in TOC and body headings ([3.1](#gma-readme-emoji)).
- [ ] No more than **three** heading levels unless justified.
- [ ] **Code fences** use the correct **language identifier** where applicable.
- [ ] **Tables** (if used): header **`#1565c0`**, aspect column **`#e3f2fd`**, body rows distinct—see [6.1](#gma-tables).
- [ ] **Mermaid** (if used): semantic colors, **`font-size:9px`**, consistent **`stroke-width`**—see [6.2](#gma-mermaid).
- [ ] Inline color/HTML extras stay **few** and purposeful—not the default for every line.
- [ ] **`README.md` on GitHub:** prose keywords use **bold** / `` `code` `` / links—not `<span style="color:…">` ([§7](#gma-inline-color)).
